The paper presents a novel neural architecture for modeling complex event sequences in temporal knowledge graphs, which involves learning representations of graph-structured data that are dynamically evolving. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Databases (cs.DB), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper proposes a new neural architecture for learning representations of dynamic graph-structured data, which is a common topic in both fields. The paper also involves predicting forthcoming events in temporal knowledge graphs, which could be relevant to cs.CL and cs.SI. Finally, the paper uses public TKG datasets for experiments, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DB.
